Japanese embassy in Jakarta receives bomb threat . The Japanese embassy in Jakarta was evacuated on Wednesday morning following a telephoned bomb threat from an anonymous caller , an embassy official said . " Someone made a phone call at 8 : 25 a . m . ( 0125 GMT ) to the office saying they were going to bomb our embassy in an hour . Nothing has happened yet , " the official , who asked not to be named , said . He said embassy staff , including ambassador Taizo Watanabe , had moved to the information centre next to the main building . A search of the embassy was under way , but " we haven ' t found anything so far , " the official said . 
